cs.CG, cs.DM, cs.DS, cs.GR, cs.SI. 

This paper deals with a problem in computational geometry, specifically the Hamiltonicity of Gabriel graphs. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The problem also involves graph theory and combinatorics, which suggests cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the properties of geometric graphs, which falls under cs.GR (Graphics) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
